  m_Name: FomoSO 5
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FomoFirewallSO
  Question: Gold reaches a six-month high.
  Desc: Investors are buying gold due to economic uncertainty.
  cmt1: Gold never goes down
  cmt2: Buy before it reaches another record!
  cmt3: Safe money
  CorrectOption: 1
  CorrectWhatHappenDec: You waited for the market to confirm the trend before investing.
    Gold experienced a short pullback, giving patient investors a better buying opportunity.
  CorrectLesson: Patience is an important investing skill. Waiting for confirmation
    can help you avoid buying at temporary price peaks.
  WrongWhatHappenDec: You bought immediately after seeing gold reach a new high.
    Shortly afterward, the price pulled back as many investors took profits.
  WrongLesson: Even strong assets experience temporary declines. Avoid assuming that
    prices will continue rising without interruption.
